Requirements

- git
- python 2.6
- virtualenv
- tcpdump is required to generate new traces
- autoconf, libtool, make, gcc, and libevent 2.0 are required to build obfsproxy
- cmake is required to build sniffjoke
- R with coda package (r-cran-coda) and jags are required to run detectors

Installation

Run ./bootstrap.py to set up the virtualenv and run "paver prepare".
To activate the virtualenv, run "source bin/activate".
Run paver tasks. Use "paver help" to see the full list of tasks.
  To start with, try "paver capture" to generate some traces.
To deactivate the virtualenv, run "deactivate".

The virtualenv contains paver and all of the necessary python libraries.
